\section{WACC Computation}

\[
\text{WACC} =
(0.5455 \times 0.09) + 
(0.1364 \times 0.065) +
(0.1818 \times 0.04) +
(0.0909 \times 0.036) +
(0.0455 \times 0.0825)
\]

\[
\text{WACC} = 4.91\%
\]

\section*{Conclusion}
The company has an estimated Weighted Average Cost of Capital of \textbf{4.91\%}. This figure can now be applied in investment appraisal decisions such as Net Present Value (NPV) and business valuation.

